result.execSummary:
The defendant Carrie L Leamy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF420, 15CM326 & 15CM328 called together at 10:49 am [Clerk SH]

ADA Shock submits victim impact statement for case 15CF420
On Motion of the State, the Court AMENDS Count #1 to Retail Theft a Class A Misdemeanor, contrary to 943.50(1m)(b) & (4)(a) - 15CF420

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered Counts #1 & #2-15CF420, Count #1-15CM326; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Case 15CM328 and Counts #3 & #4-15CF420 

On Counts #1 & #2-15CF420, Count #1-15CM326, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
